---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "About UlamPinoy | The Filipino Family Kitchen Chronicles";
const pageDescription = "Meet the family behind UlamPinoy, sharing authentic Filipino recipes and kitchen stories from our home in Spain to yours.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <main class="bg-white pt-24 pb-16">
    {/* Hero Section */}
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-white py-16 md:py-24">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h1 class="savate-heavy text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-amber-600 mb-6">
            Kumusta Kaibigan! üëã
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            We're a Filipino family living in Spain, cooking our way through homesickness one recipe at a time.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8 md:p-12 flex flex-col justify-center">
              <p class="text-amber-600 font-medium mb-4">OUR STORY</p>
              <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mb-6">
                From Our Kitchen to Yours
              </h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Ulampinoy started as our digital recipe diary and somehow evolved into a
                full-blown family cooking empire (well, maybe not empire, but we do have
                matching aprons now).
              </p>
              <div class="flex space-x-4">
                <a 
                  href="#our-story" 
                  class="px-6 py-3 bg-amber-500 text-white rounded-full font-medium hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors"
                >
                  Our Journey
                </a>
                <a 
                  href="/recipes" 
                  class="px-6 py-3 border-2 border-amber-500 text-amber-600 rounded-full font-medium hover:bg-amber-50 transition-colors"
                >
                  Browse Recipes
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 h-64 md:h-auto bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-100 to-amber-200 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-6xl">üçõ</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Origin Story */}
    <section id="our-story" class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="text-amber-500 text-lg font-medium">üìñ OUR ORIGIN STORY</span>
          <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mt-2">
            The Manila-Madrid Connection
          </h2>
          <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-amber-400 mx-auto mt-4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-600">
          <p>
            Once upon a time, we migrated to Spain and realized that decent Filipino food was rarer than parking spaces in
            Madrid. Like millions of Filipinos around the world, we're part of the beautiful
            diaspora that carries our culture, traditions, and most importantly, our recipes
            wherever we go.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            There's something beautifully full-circle about the
            Manila-Madrid connection ‚Äì centuries of shared history through colonial ties and
            cultural exchange, and now here we are, modern Filipinos in Spain sharing our
            heritage through kitchen stories and YouTube videos.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-amber-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-amber-400 my-8">
            <p class="text-amber-800 italic">
              "When our kids grow up and can't tell adobo from adobe, they'll have 60+ videos
              to save their culinary souls."
            </p>
          </div>

          <p>
            So we did what any sensible Filipino family would do: we started cooking everything ourselves and
            documenting it obsessively. What began as a simple food journal quickly
            transformed into our <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/ulampinoy/featured" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium">YouTube cooking channel</a> ‚Äì a family project
            that serves as both entertainment and insurance policy.
          </p>

          <p>
            Every recipe comes with stories, memories, and the
            occasional kitchen disaster (which we may or may not include in the final cut).
            You can find all our <a href="/videos" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium">video recipes</a> organized by category, or if
            you're scratching your head wondering what "gata" or "patis" means, our handy
            <a href="/glossary" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium">glossary</a> has got your back with translations and explanations of
            Filipino cooking terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-500 to-amber-600 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl text-center">
          <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-2">61,463+ Subscribers</p>
          <p class="text-amber-100">and over 9.9 million video views and counting!</p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-amber-100">Apparently, we're not the only ones who miss home cooking!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Mission Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="text-amber-500 text-lg font-medium">üéØ OUR MISSION</span>
          <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mt-2">
            More Than Just Recipes
          </h2>
          <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-amber-400 mx-auto mt-4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-600">
          <p>
            We're building the ultimate Filipino family cookbook, one video at a time. Our
            goal is simple: create a collection of tried-and-tested recipes with our own
            family twist, presented in a way that won't put you to sleep (unlike your
            typical cooking show).
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Beyond recipes, we share discoveries, lessons learned,
            random kitchen wisdom, and whatever else catches our fancy in our <a href="/articles" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium">articles
            section</a>. Think of us as your Filipino cooking uncles and titas who
            happen to live in Spain and know way too much about proper rice-to-water ratios.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Tech Stack Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="text-amber-500 text-lg font-medium">üõ†Ô∏è THE TECH STACK</span>
          <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mt-2">
            Behind the Scenes
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-4">This website is lovingly crafted and occasionally cursed at, built with:</p>
          <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-amber-400 mx-auto mt-4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Tech Stack</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">‚Ä¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">AstroJS</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Because we upgraded from Eleventy and now our build times are faster than cooking minute rice</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">‚Ä¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">Netlify</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Our deployment heroes who keep us online (salamat!)</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">‚Ä¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">GitHub</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Where our code lives and where we backup our digital kitchen secrets</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">‚Ä¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">Google Fonts</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Making our text look prettier than our food photography</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-amber-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Special Thanks</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              Special shoutout to our friends at Netlify for their generous hosting. Without them,
              this site would be as inaccessible as finding good balut in Barcelona.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Also, big thanks to our taste testers (a.k.a. our long-suffering family members) 
              who bravely eat everything we cook, no matter how experimental.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* CTA Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-amber-600 text-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl text-center">
        <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6">Let's Cook Together!</h2>
        <p class="text-xl mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-amber-100">
          Have a recipe request? Want to argue about the proper way to cook
          adobo? Just want to say hi? We'd love to hear from you!
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
          <a 
            href="/contact" 
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-full text-amber-700 bg-white hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors"
          >
            Get in Touch
          </a>
          <a 
            href="/videos" 
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border-2 border-white text-base font-medium rounded-full text-white hover:bg-white hover:bg-opacity-10 transition-colors"
          >
            Watch Our Videos
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-amber-500">
          <p class="text-amber-200 text-sm italic">
            *P.S. - If you're wondering about the name "Ulampinoy," it's a portmanteau of
            "ulam" (Filipino for viand/main dish) and "Pinoy" (colloquial term for
            Filipino). Yes, we're that creative with our naming conventions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
